dataqual.logic: This parcel layer contains discrete, non-overlapping polygons for each property. Adjacent polygons with common ownership and a single tax record have been retained in the "OthLeg" layer that accompanies this TaxPar layer, and dissolved into single parcels in this TaxPar layer. Some non-adjacent parcels may be represented by multi-part polygons where they share common ownership and a single tax record. Public right of ways exist as polygons, not null space. Linework associated with private ROWs are retained in the "OthLeg" layer. Water polygons also representing parcel boundaries have been retained in this TaxPar layer. Additional water features that are not considered parcel boundaries may have been placed in the "Misc" layer that accompanies this TaxPar layer. Easements and other similar non-fee taxable boundaries exist in the 'OthLeg" layer, not the TaxPar layer.

srcinfo.srccontr: Source data is MassGIS Level II-compliant digital parcel file, in ESRI personal geodatabase format. This geodatabase was originally automated using ESRI ArcGIS 9.2.1 in May 2006 from hardcopy assessor's tax maps which were scanned and georeferenced to the 2005 MassGIS orthophotos.

procstep.procdesc: Existing Level II parcel data was converted to MassGIS Level 3 template geodatabase and additional data layers and tables were added.
Spatial accuracy of data was verified using the parcel standard guidelines; town boundary was verified to be coincident with MassGIS Town Boundary layer. Polygon topology was updated and validated.

Multi-part polygons were created where necessary; internal polygon boundaries were dissolved where necessary; polygons representing legal boundaries such as easements or private right-of-ways were created. LOC_ID was updated
Parcel updates were completed. CAMA data was matched against parcel data to produce a mismatch report which was reconciled with the help of the town Assessor. Final QAQC tools were run.

overview.dsoverv: Tax parcel polygons for Rehoboth, MA. This data set contains polygons which delineate property ownership in the town of Rehoboth, according to the assessor's tax maps as of March 2011. It is formatted in compliance with the MassGIS Standard for Digital Parcel Files, Version 2.0. This data set is considered to be MassGIS Level III-compliant and is derived from an upgrade of the previous Level II-compliant version of this same data set.
